Things seem to be looking up in the fight against COVID-19. South Africa has moved back to level one, after emerging from the second wave. Curfew hours have been reduced and gatherings are permitted under strict regulations. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The hospitality industry is welcoming the eased lockdown regulations. Small business owners say there is now some hope they will be able to save jobs. READ: SUMMARY: South Africa moves to Lockdown Level 1 President Cyril Ramaphosa moved the country to lockdown level one from adjusted level three on Sunday night. Phase two of the COVID-19 vaccine roll-out will begin in late April or early May.